    • Constructor Detail

      • GenericObjectPool

        public GenericObjectPool(PooledObjectFactory<T> factory)
        Constructs an object with an Integer.MAX_VALUE limit on the number of active or inactive objects. The pool uses factory to construct objects. The pool retains a minimum of zero inactive objects.
        Parameters:
        factory - - an object factory

      • GenericObjectPool

        public GenericObjectPool(PooledObjectFactory<T> factory,
                 int minInactive,
                 int maxInactive,
                 int maxActive)
        Constructs an object pool with that limits the number of inactive and active objects. The pool uses factory to construct up to maxActive objects. The pool retains up to maxInactive objects. The acquire method blocks until an object is released if there are already maxActive number of active objects. The release method destroys an object if there are already a maxInactive number of inactive objects.
        Parameters:
        factory - - an object factory
        minInactive - - minimum number of inactive objects that will be retained by the pool by the reap(Condition) method.
        maxInactive - - maximum number of inactive objects that will be retained by the pool.
        maxActive - - maximum number of active objects that may be acquired from the pool.
